<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06101090 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06101090 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  FARM; BIRD; RECIPE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  THERE is nothing worse than trying to go on a diet when no one else in thefamily needs to or is interested. It usually means that you'll prepare aseparate meal for yourself and do double-duty cooking.;    Fortunately, thereare some dishes that the whole family can appreciate and you don't even haveto tell them that they are low in calories. Chicken is a good place to startbecause, without the skin, it is naturally low in fat.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Food  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MICROWAVED CHICKEN DIJON IS LOW-FAT DISHFOR WHOLE FAMILY  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Marcia Cone and Thelma Snyder are authors of 'Microwave Entertaining&quot; (Simon andamp;Schuster, $29.95).  </MEMO><TEXT>      CHICKEN DIJON;  1 teaspoon olive oil;  2 cloves garlic, minced;  2 greenonions, thinly sliced;  2 tablespoons dry white wine or vermouth;  1tablespoon fresh lemon juice;  1/4 cup Dijon mustard;  1 teaspoon freshlychopped tarragon or 1/4 teaspoon dried;   Dash freshly ground pepper;  4(4-ounce) skinless, boneless chicken breasts;   Combine oil, garlic and greenonions in 10-inch pie plate. Cook on high 1 minute. Stir in wine, lemon juice,mustard, tarragon and pepper to taste. Roll chicken in mixture and placebreasts around outer rim of dish. Cover with wax paper and microwave on high 3minutes.;    Turn chicken over and spoon some sauce over top. Cover again andmicrowave on high 3 to 5 minutes more or until chicken is opaque but stilltender. Let stand 3 minutes. Serve each chicken breast with juices spooned ontop. Makes 4 servings at 155 calories per serving.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  MARCIA CONE AND THELMA SNYDER  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910410  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  244  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday April 10, 199100101090,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>